# Backend Conventions

## Language & Style
- Python 3.12, async/await throughout — never use sync blocking I/O in async endpoints
- All route handlers are `async def`; DB ops use `await session.execute(...)`, Claude calls are awaited
- Use Pydantic v2 for all request/response validation and for LLM structured outputs
- Never hardcode secrets; always read from `app.config.settings`
- No `print()` in application code; use `logging` or FastAPI's built-in logger

## Project layout (`backend/app/`)
- `main.py` — app factory + lifespan, no business logic
- `config.py` — all env-based settings (pydantic-settings)
- `db.py` — async engine/session factory, `get_session` FastAPI dependency
- `models.py` — SQLAlchemy 2.0 models only (no logic)
- `schemas.py` — Pydantic models only (no logic)
- `routers/` — HTTP layer; delegate immediately to services
- `services/` — all business logic lives here

## Error handling
- Raise `HTTPException` in routers; services raise plain Python exceptions
- Never swallow exceptions silently; always log before re-raising
- Claude service must handle `anthropic.APIError` and bubble up a descriptive message

## Database
- Async SQLAlchemy 2.0 — `AsyncSession`, `AsyncEngine`, `select()` style
- Pass `AsyncSession` via `Depends(get_session)` — never import session globally
- Use `await session.commit()` and `await session.refresh(obj)` after writes

## Commands
```bash
cd backend
uv sync                  # install deps
uv run uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000
uv run ruff check .      # lint
uv run ruff format .     # format
uv run pyright           # type check
uv run python -m app.seed  # load sample data
```
